range(x) returns the decimal exponent range of x.

integer examples:
ia(i) = 0  range(ia(i)) = 9
ia(i) = 1  range(ia(i)) = 9
ia(i) = -1  range(ia(i)) = 9
ia(i) = 100  range(ia(i)) = 9

integer kind examples:
range(0)   = 9
range(0_1) = 2
range(0_2) = 4
range(0_4) = 9
range(0_8) = 18

real examples:
ra(i) = 0  range(ra(i)) = 37
ra(i) = 1  range(ra(i)) = 37
ra(i) = -1  range(ra(i)) = 37
ra(i) = 100  range(ra(i)) = 37

real kind examples:
range(1.0)   = 37
range(1.0_4) = 37
range(1.0_8) = 307

complex examples:
range((1.0, 2.0))     = 37
range((1.0_4, 2.0_4)) = 37
range((1.0_8, 2.0_8)) = 307
